import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import pandas as pd
import time

def get_weekly_plan(plan_number):
    """
    Scrapes a weekly meal plan from the website.
    
    Args:
        plan_number: Integer between 100-210 representing the meal plan number
    
    Returns:
        Dictionary with day names as keys and recipe names as values
    """
    url = f"https://tastesbetterfromscratch.com/meal-plan-{plan_number}/"
    headers = {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64)"}
    
    response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, "html.parser")
    
    # Find paragraphs with meal plan content
    paragraphs = soup.find_all("p", attrs={"class": "has-text-align-left"})
    
    # Dictionary to store day: recipe pairs
    meal_plan = {}
    days = ["Monday", "Tuesday", "Wednesday", "Thursday", "Friday", "Saturday", "Sunday"]
    
    for p in paragraphs:
        text = p.get_text(strip=True)
        
        # Check if this paragraph contains a day of the week
        for day in days:
            if day in text or day.upper() in text:
                # Extract recipe name (remove day label and clean up)
                recipe_name = text.replace(f"{day}:", "").replace(day.upper(), "").strip()
                # Remove anything in parentheses
                recipe_name = recipe_name.split("(")[0].strip()
                # Remove extra punctuation
                recipe_name = recipe_name.rstrip(":").strip()
                
                meal_plan[day] = recipe_name
                break
    
    return meal_plan


def match_recipe(recipe_name, api_key):
    """
    Searches the Tasty API for recipes matching the given name.
    
    Args:
        recipe_name: String name of the recipe to search for
        api_key: RapidAPI key for authentication
    
    Returns:
        List of dictionaries containing recipe information
    """
    if not recipe_name or recipe_name == "":
        return []
    
    url = "https://tasty.p.rapidapi.com/recipes/list"
    headers = {
        "X-RapidAPI-Key": api_key,
        "X-RapidAPI-Host": "tasty.p.rapidapi.com"
    }
    params = {
        "from": "0",
        "size": "100",
        "q": recipe_name
    }
    
    try:
        response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, params=params)
        data = response.json()
        
        recipes = []
        if "results" in data:
            for recipe in data["results"]:
                recipes.append({
                    "Name": recipe.get("name", "N/A"),
                    "Description": recipe.get("description", "N/A"),
                    "Prep Time (min)": recipe.get("prep_time_minutes", "N/A"),
                    "Cook Time (min)": recipe.get("cook_time_minutes", "N/A"),
                    "Servings": recipe.get("num_servings", "N/A"),
                    "URL": recipe.get("original_video_url", "N/A")
                })
        
        return recipes
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"Error fetching recipes for '{recipe_name}': {e}")
        return []


def get_mealplan_data(plan_number):
    """
    Gets meal plan and matches all recipes with Tasty API.
    
    Args:
        plan_number: Integer between 100-210 representing the meal plan number
    
    Returns:
        DataFrame containing all matched recipes with meal plan day information
    """
    api_key = "f442d263abmsh6225aca3d351484p1578c1jsn71aa624d5f7f"
    
    # Get the weekly meal plan
    print(f"Fetching meal plan {plan_number}...")
    meal_plan = get_weekly_plan(plan_number)
    
    if not meal_plan:
        print("No meal plan found!")
        return pd.DataFrame()
    
    print(f"Found {len(meal_plan)} days in meal plan")
    
    # Search for each recipe
    all_recipes = []
    
    for day, recipe_name in meal_plan.items():
        print(f"\nSearching for {day}: {recipe_name}")
        
        # Add a small delay to avoid rate limiting
        time.sleep(0.5)
        
        matched_recipes = match_recipe(recipe_name, api_key)
        
        # Add day and original recipe name to each matched recipe
        for recipe in matched_recipes:
            recipe["Day"] = day
            recipe["Original Recipe"] = recipe_name
            all_recipes.append(recipe)
        
        print(f"  Found {len(matched_recipes)} matches")
    
    # Create DataFrame
    df = pd.DataFrame(all_recipes)
    
    # Reorder columns to put Day and Original Recipe first
    if not df.empty:
        cols = ["Day", "Original Recipe"] + [col for col in df.columns if col not in ["Day", "Original Recipe"]]
        df = df[cols]
    
    print(f"\nTotal recipes found: {len(df)}")
    
    return df

def is_vegetarian(recipe_name):
    """
    Determines if a recipe is vegetarian based on meat keywords in the title.
    
    Args:
        recipe_name: String name of the recipe
    
    Returns:
        Boolean - True if vegetarian (no meat detected), False otherwise
    """
    if not recipe_name or recipe_name == "N/A":
        return None
    
    # Convert to lowercase for case-insensitive matching
    recipe_lower = recipe_name.lower()
    
    # List of common meat keywords
    meat_keywords = [
        'chicken', 'beef', 'pork', 'turkey', 'duck', 'lamb', 'veal',
        'bacon', 'sausage', 'ham', 'salami', 'pepperoni', 'prosciutto',
        'fish', 'salmon', 'tuna', 'cod', 'tilapia', 'shrimp', 'prawns',
        'crab', 'lobster', 'scallop', 'clam', 'mussel', 'oyster',
        'anchovy', 'sardine', 'meat', 'steak', 'ribs', 'brisket',
        'meatball', 'meatloaf', 'bolognese', 'carnitas', 'chorizo',
        'venison', 'bison', 'rabbit', 'goose', 'pheasant', 'quail'
    ]
    
    # Check if any meat keyword is in the recipe name
    for meat in meat_keywords:
        if meat in recipe_lower:
            return False
    
    return True

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import requests
import pandas as pd
import time

def get_mealplan_with_nutrition(plan_number):
    """
    Gets meal plan with full nutrition data.
    """
    api_key = "f442d263abmsh6225aca3d351484p1578c1jsn71aa624d5f7f"
    
    # Get the weekly meal plan
    print(f"Fetching meal plan {plan_number} with nutrition data...")
    meal_plan = get_weekly_plan(plan_number)
    
    all_recipes = []
    
    for day, recipe_name in meal_plan.items():
        print(f"Searching for {day}: {recipe_name}")
        time.sleep(0.5)
        
        url = "https://tasty.p.rapidapi.com/recipes/list"
        headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": api_key,
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "tasty.p.rapidapi.com"
        }
        params = {"from": "0", "size": "20", "q": recipe_name}
        
        try:
            response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, params=params)
            data = response.json()
            
            if "results" in data and len(data["results"]) > 0:
                # Take the first (best) match
                recipe = data["results"][0]
                nutrition = recipe.get('nutrition', {})
                
                recipe_info = {
                    "Day": day,
                    "Original Recipe": recipe_name,
                    "Name": recipe.get("name", "N/A"),
                    "Calories": nutrition.get('calories', 0) if nutrition else 0,
                    "Fat (g)": nutrition.get('fat', 0) if nutrition else 0,
                    "Carbs (g)": nutrition.get('carbohydrates', 0) if nutrition else 0,
                    "Protein (g)": nutrition.get('protein', 0) if nutrition else 0,
                    "Fiber (g)": nutrition.get('fiber', 0) if nutrition else 0,
                    "Sugar (g)": nutrition.get('sugar', 0) if nutrition else 0,
                    "Vegetarian": is_vegetarian(recipe.get("name", ""))
                }
                
                all_recipes.append(recipe_info)
                print(f"  â Found with nutrition data")
            else:
                print(f"  â No matches found")
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"  â Error: {e}")
    
    df = pd.DataFrame(all_recipes)
    
    # Order by days of the week
    day_order = ["Monday", "Tuesday", "Wednesday", "Thursday", "Friday", "Saturday", "Sunday"]
    df['Day'] = pd.Categorical(df['Day'], categories=day_order, ordered=True)
    df = df.sort_values('Day')
    
    return df


# Get the data with nutrition information
nutrition_df = get_mealplan_with_nutrition(202)

# Create a simple visualization
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 8))

# Define colors for vegetarian vs non-vegetarian
colors = ['#2ecc71' if veg else '#e74c3c' for veg in nutrition_df['Vegetarian']]
days = nutrition_df['Day'].astype(str)

# Plot 1: Calories by day with vegetarian indicator
bars = ax1.bar(days, nutrition_df['Calories'], color=colors, alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
ax1.set_title('Meal Plan 202: Daily Calories (Green=Vegetarian, Red=Non-Vegetarian)', 
              fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
ax1.set_ylabel('Calories', fontsize=12)
ax1.set_xlabel('Day of Week', fontsize=12)
ax1.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)

# Add calorie values on bars
for bar in bars:
    height = bar.get_height()
    if height > 0:
        ax1.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height,
                f'{int(height)}',
                ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)

# Plot 2: Protein, Carbs, and Fat
x_pos = np.arange(len(days))
width = 0.25

ax2.bar(x_pos - width, nutrition_df['Protein (g)'], width, 
        label='Protein', color='#3498db', alpha=0.7)
ax2.bar(x_pos, nutrition_df['Carbs (g)'], width, 
        label='Carbs', color='#f39c12', alpha=0.7)
ax2.bar(x_pos + width, nutrition_df['Fat (g)'], width, 
        label='Fat', color='#9b59b6', alpha=0.7)

ax2.set_title('Macronutrients by Day', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
ax2.set_ylabel('Grams', fontsize=12)
ax2.set_xlabel('Day of Week', fontsize=12)
ax2.set_xticks(x_pos)
ax2.set_xticklabels(days, rotation=45, ha='right')
ax2.legend()
ax2.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('mealplan_202_simple.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()
